How do we collect Personal Information?

Most of the Personal Information we collect comes directly from you, either through email, telephone, the buildertrend.com website, or the Solution. However, we may also collect information about you from other sources, including but not limited to third parties from whom we have purchased Personal Information. This helps us update, expand, and analyze our records, identify new customers, and create more tailored advertising to provide services that may be of interest to you. In particular, we collect Personal Information from the following sources:

Buildertrend customers who may supply information directly to us, including Personal Information regarding their own business, clients, contacts, or sub-contractors;
From publicly accessible sources, such as property or permit records, corporate websites, trade and business licenses, professional certifications, permits, trade association membership, and e-commerce marketplace profiles (from these sources, we may obtain business information on both business people and companies);
Directly from third party providers of business information, such as home marketing sources, social media profiles, or customer due diligence providers;
From a third party with your consent, such as a financial providers;
From cookies on our website (see our Cookie Policy for more information); and
From market research surveys and/or interviews conducted by our own employees or by third-party vendors.

We may share your Personal Information with:

Our affiliates, subsidiaries, advisors, and consultants;
Our contracted service providers, who provide services such as IT and system administration and hosting, credit card processing, research and analytics, marketing, customer support, and data enrichment for the purposes and pursuant to the legal bases described above;
If you use our services as an Authorized User (as defined in the Buildertrend Terms and Conditions), with the affiliated customer responsible for your access to the services to the extent this is necessary for verifying accounts and activity, investigating suspicious activity, or enforcing our terms and policies;
Third parties approved by you, including social media sites you choose to link your account to or third-party payment providers;
Our contracted joint marketing partners and other business partners, who may process your Personal Information for purposes such as marketing and providing products and services that may be of interest to you and/or your business;
If we are involved in a merger, reorganization, dissolution or other fundamental corporate change, or sell a website or business unit, or if all or a portion of our business, assets or stock are acquired by third party, with such third party. In accordance with applicable laws, we will use reasonable efforts to notify you of any transfer of Personal Information to an unaffiliated third party;
Law enforcement, public, and government authorities, and other entities as we deem reasonably necessary to comply with law, support investigations, and protect the rights and property of you, us, and others.
We may also collect, process, and use non-personal, aggregated, or anonymized data in any way, including by disclosing, sharing, or otherwise making it available to third parties for various research, marketing, analytics, and measurement purposes. Additionally, Buildertrend may share such anonymous usage on an aggregate basis in the normal course of operating our business. This may include, but is not limited to, sharing information publicly to show the general use of our services.

Any Personal Information or other information you choose to submit in communities, forums, blogs, or chat rooms on our websites may be read, collected, and used by others who visit these forums.

We only allow our service providers and joint marketing partners to handle your Personal Information if we are satisfied that they take appropriate measures to protect your Personal Information. We also impose contractual obligations on service providers and joint marketing partners to ensure they can only use your personal information for the purposes outlined in our contracts.

Residents of California have the right to know the Personal Information Buildertrend collects, uses, discloses, or sells.  Specifically, you have the right to know:
The categories of Personal Information we have collected about you;
The categories of sources from which the Personal Information is collected;
Our business or commercial purpose for collecting, selling, or sharing Personal Information;
The categories of third parties with whom we share Personal Information, if any; and
The specific pieces of Personal Information we have collected about you.

Subject to certain exceptions set out below, on receipt of a verifiable request from you, we will:

Delete your Personal Information from our records; and

Direct any service providers to delete your Personal Information from their records.

Please note that we may not delete your Personal Information if it is necessary to:

Complete the transaction for which the Personal Information was collected, fulfill the terms of a written warranty or product recall conducted in accordance with federal law, provide a good or service requested by you, or reasonably anticipated within the context of our ongoing business relationship with you, or otherwise perform a contract between you and us;
Detect security incidents, protect against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity; or prosecute those responsible for that activity;

Debug to identify and repair errors that impair existing intended functionality;

Exercise free speech, ensure the right of another consumer to exercise his or her right of free speech, or exercise another right provided for by law;

Comply with the California Electronic Communications Privacy Act;

Engage in public or peer-reviewed scientific, historical, or statistical research in the public interest that adheres to all other applicable ethics and privacy laws, when our deletion of the information is likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of such research, provided we have obtained your informed consent;

Enable solely internal uses that are reasonably aligned with your expectations based on your relationship with us;

Comply with an existing legal obligation; or

Otherwise use your personal information, internally, in a lawful manner that is compatible with the context in which you provided the information.

